<subSubSection id="C32365407A48FFBA83E6F831FCE0F7DE" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B8636CB7A48FFBA83E6F831FCE0F7DE" blockId="6.[136,1452,1953,2088]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A48FFBA83E6F831FE44F842" box="[189,456,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Culture characteristics:</emphasis>
Colonies developing on PDA are incubated at room temperature and reach a diameter of 
<quantity id="4CC19B2E7A48FFBA83D3F855FF5BF819" box="[136,215,1989,2016]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
after 15 days, flat, spreading, with a fluffy, moderately mouse-gray mycelium. Surface lightly rough with pale gray hyphae, colonies somewhat sunken in the middle, and with an irregular edge. The reverse side dark brown but pale brown at the margins, lobate at the center and not pigmented.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
