<subSubSection id="C32365407A49FFBB83E6FEBFFD70FD74" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8636CB7A49FFBB83E6FEBFFD70FD74" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,653]" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB83E6FEBFFD3FFEB1" box="[189,691,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">
Notes: 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB824AFEBEFD3FFEB1" authorityName="X. Tang, R. S. Jayaward., K. D. Hyde, &amp; J. C. Kang" authorityYear="2022" box="[273,691,302,328]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dipterocarpicola">Pseudoplagiostoma dipterocarpicola</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
forms a clade with 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB80FBFEBFFBB2FEB1" box="[928,1086,302,328]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mangiferae">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB80FBFEBFFBB2FEB1" box="[928,1086,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">P. mangiferae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with highly support (78% ML, 68% MP and 1 BYPP), but 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB829CFEC3FD2CFE95" authorityName="X. Tang, R. S. Jayaward., K. D. Hyde, &amp; J. C. Kang" authorityYear="2022" box="[455,672,338,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dipterocarpicola">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB829CFEC3FD2CFE95" box="[455,672,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">P. dipterocarpicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB8779FEC3FB33FE95" box="[1058,1215,338,364]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mangiferae">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB8779FEC3FB33FE95" box="[1058,1215,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">P. mangiferae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB8795FEC2FECFFE69" authorityName="X. Tang, R. S. Jayaward., K. D. Hyde, &amp; J. C. Kang" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dipterocarpicola">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB8795FEC2FECFFE69" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">Pseudoplagiostoma dipterocarpicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark brown, conidiomata with a thick wall at the base, 
<specimenCount id="9D3FFD427A49FFBB80B5FEE7FBD7FE68" box="[1006,1115,375,401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of conidiogenous cells, these ranging from cylindrical with a long, slimy cylindrical neck to ampulliform and wider at the base, straight, short and without paraphyses, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB815EFE2FFD2EFE21" box="[517,674,446,472]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mangiferae">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB815EFE2FFD2EFE21" box="[517,674,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">P. mangiferae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a yellowish brown conidiomata wall, cylindrical to ampulliform conidiomata that are wider at the base, straight conidiogenous cells and paraphyses (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA84B3A7A49FFBB8738FE72FA2CFE05" author="Cheewangkoon, R. &amp; Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Verkley, G. J. M. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; Wingfield, M. J. &amp; Gryzenhout, M. &amp; Summerell, B. A. &amp; Denman, S. &amp; Toanun, C. &amp; Crous, P. W." box="[1123,1440,482,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" pagination="89 - 105" refId="ref5553" refString="Cheewangkoon, R., Groenewald, J. Z., Verkley, G. J. M., Hyde, K. D., Wingfield, M. J., Gryzenhout, M., Summerell, B. A., Denman, S., Toanun, C. &amp; Crous, P. W. (2010) Re-evaluation of Cryptosporiopsis eucalypti and Cryptosporiopsis - like species occurring on Eucalyptus leaves. Fungal Diversity 44: 89 - 105. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 010 - 0041 - 5" type="journal article" year="2010">
Cheewangkoon 
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB8646FE73FADEFE05" box="[1309,1362,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Based on pairwise nucleotide comparisons, 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB81D8FD97FCD0FDD9" authorityName="X. Tang, R. S. Jayaward., K. D. Hyde, &amp; J. C. Kang" authorityYear="2022" box="[643,860,518,544]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dipterocarpicola">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB81D8FD97FCD0FDD9" box="[643,860,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">P. dipterocarpicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB8775FD97FB40FDD9" box="[1070,1228,518,544]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mangiferae">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB8775FD97FB40FDD9" box="[1070,1228,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">P. mangiferae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 31/620 bp (3%) in ITS, 7/814 (0.98%) in LSU, 63/410 bp (15%) in 
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB81B5FDBAFCA3FDBD" box="[750,815,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">tef1-α</emphasis>
and 87/450 (19%) in 
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB8763FDBAFBE7FDBD" box="[1080,1131,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">tub2</emphasis>
. Based on the combination of morphological characters and multigene phylogeny, we describe 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D487A49FFBB80CFFDDFFBE1FD91" authorityName="X. Tang, R. S. Jayaward., K. D. Hyde, &amp; J. C. Kang" authorityYear="2022" box="[916,1133,590,616]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pseudoplagiostomataceae" genus="Pseudoplagiostoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dipterocarpicola">
<emphasis id="B94DEAD97A49FFBB80CFFDDFFBE1FD91" box="[916,1133,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="240">P. dipterocarpicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein as a distinct species according to the guidelines of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA84B3A7A49FFBB8287FDE3FD74FD74" author="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[476,760,626,653]" pageId="7" pageNumber="240" pagination="1669 - 1677" refId="ref8309" refString="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2016) Establishing species boundaries and new taxa among fungi: recommendations to resolve taxonomic ambiguities. Mycosphere 7: 1669 - 1677. https: // doi. org / 10.5943 / mycosphere / 7 / 11 / 4" type="journal article" year="2016">Jeewon and Hyde (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
